---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
import type { Lang } from '../i18n/translations';

const lang: Lang = 'en';

const GITHUB_ISSUES_URL = 'https://github.com/volodymyr4509/kulmanlab/issues';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — KulmanLab"
  description="How KulmanLab handles your data: drawings stay on your device, no accounts, no ads. Google Analytics is used for anonymous usage metrics."
  canonical="https://kulmanlab.com/privacy/"
  lang={lang}
>

  <SiteHeader lang={lang} />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">

    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="mb-3 text-4xl font-bold text-slate-50">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">Last updated: July 14, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Summary -->
    <div class="mb-12 rounded-xl border border-brand/20 bg-brand/5 p-6">
      <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-bold text-slate-50">The short version</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"></span>Your drawings are stored in your browser and never leave your device. All your work belongs to you.</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"></span>There are no accounts, no sign-up, and no email. We do not know who you are.</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"></span>We use Google Analytics to count visits and understand which features are used. It never sees your drawing content.</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"></span>The app is free and funded by ads (Google AdSense). Your drawings are never used for advertising, and we never sell your data.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">Your drawings stay on your device</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          Everything you draw in KulmanLab CAD is saved to your browser's local storage (IndexedDB) on your own
          device. Drawings are never uploaded, transmitted, or stored on any server. After the first load the app
          works fully offline — no server is involved in opening, editing, or saving your files.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because your files exist only in your browser, you are in full control of them. You can delete individual
          drawings from the <a href="/docs/commands/files/" class="text-brand hover:underline">Files panel</a>, erase
          everything at once with the <a href="/docs/commands/wipestorage/" class="text-brand hover:underline">wipestorage</a>
          command, or clear the site data in your browser settings. We cannot access, restore, or delete your files
          for you — we never have them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">No accounts, no personal data</h2>
        <p>
          KulmanLab has no login, no registration, and no email collection. We do not collect your name, email
          address, or any other information that identifies you personally, and we have nothing to sell or share.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">Analytics</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          This website (kulmanlab.com) and the app (app.kulmanlab.com) use <strong class="text-slate-100">Google
          Analytics 4</strong> to collect anonymous usage metrics. This tells us things like how many people visit,
          which pages they read, what country they are in (approximate, derived from the IP address — Google
          Analytics 4 does not store IP addresses), and what browser and device type they use.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-3">On the website we also record a few anonymous interaction events:</p>
        <ul class="mb-3 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-slate-500"></span>clicks on "Launch App" and similar buttons,</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-slate-500"></span>clicks on outbound links (the destination address of the link),</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-slate-500"></span>how far down a page you scroll, and the interface language you use.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          None of this includes your drawing content, file names, or anything you create in the app. Analytics data
          is processed by Google under the
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">Advertising</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          The app (app.kulmanlab.com) is free to use and is funded by ads served through
          <strong class="text-slate-100">Google AdSense</strong>. This website (kulmanlab.com) does not show ads.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-3">
          Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this or
          other websites. Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to show you ads based on
          your visits to the app and/or other sites on the Internet. Ads are selected by Google — they never see
          your drawing content, file names, or anything you create in the app.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can opt out of personalized advertising in Google's
          <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Ads Settings</a>,
          or opt out of third-party advertising cookies more broadly at
          <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">aboutads.info</a>
          (or <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.eu" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">youronlinechoices.eu</a> in Europe).
          How Google uses data from sites that show its ads is described at
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">Cookies and local storage</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          Two kinds of cookies are used. Google Analytics sets
          <code class="text-xs font-mono text-brand bg-brand/10 border border-brand/20 rounded px-1.5 py-0.5">_ga</code>
          and <code class="text-xs font-mono text-brand bg-brand/10 border border-brand/20 rounded px-1.5 py-0.5">_ga_*</code>
          on both the website and the app — they contain a random identifier that distinguishes browsers so that
          repeat visits are not counted as new visitors, expire after up to two years, and cannot be used to
          identify you personally. In the app, Google AdSense and its advertising partners set additional
          advertising cookies to serve and measure ads, as described in the Advertising section above. There are no
          social-media cookies, and the website itself sets no advertising cookies.
        </p>
        <p>
          In addition, the website remembers your language preference and the app stores your drawings and undo
          history in browser local storage. This data never leaves your device.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">Third-party services</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">Besides Google Analytics and Google AdSense, KulmanLab relies on two infrastructure services:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-slate-500"></span><span><strong class="text-slate-100">Google Fonts</strong> — the Inter font is loaded from Google's servers. Your browser sends a standard web request (including your IP address) to Google to fetch the font files.</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-slate-500"></span><span><strong class="text-slate-100">Firebase Hosting (Google)</strong> — serves this website and the app. Like any web server, it processes standard request logs (IP address, requested URL, user agent) to deliver the pages.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">Your choices</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          If you prefer not to be counted in analytics, you can block the Google Analytics cookies in your browser,
          use a content blocker, or install the
          <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Google Analytics opt-out add-on</a>.
          The website and the app work exactly the same without analytics.
        </p>
        <p>
          For advertising, you can turn off ad personalization in
          <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Google Ads Settings</a>
          — you will still see ads in the app, but they will not be based on your interests or browsing history.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If our data practices change — for example, if a new third-party service is added — this page will be
          updated and the date at the top revised.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold text-slate-50">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about privacy? Open an issue on
          <a href={GITHUB_ISSUES_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">GitHub</a>
          or ask in the <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/kulmanlab/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand hover:underline">Reddit community</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>

  </main>

  <SiteFooter lang={lang} />

</Layout>
